The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at an event in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. Pence praised the state for electing President Trump and passing historic tax cuts. He highlighted the administration's achievements in the military, international relations, and domestic security. Pence also emphasized the administration's efforts to roll back regulations, promote American manufacturing, and create jobs. He criticized Senator Bob Casey for voting against the tax cuts and other policies. Pence pledged to continue fighting for the people of Pennsylvania and outlined the administration's agenda for the future, including infrastructure, immigration, and addressing the opioid crisis. He encouraged the audience to have faith and continue supporting the President's agenda.